<inglise> Decision Regarding Cases Where Customs </inglise>
<eesti> vl43 RT II 1999, 22, 123 </eesti>
<inglise> Administrations Have Reasons to Doubt the Truth or Accuracy of the Declared Value </inglise>
<eesti> OTSUS JUHTUMITE KOHTA, KUS TOLLIL ON P&Otilde;HJUST KAHELDA DEKLAREERITUD V&Auml;&Auml;RTUSE &Otilde;IGSUSES V&Otilde;I T&Auml;PSUSES </eesti>
<inglise> Ministers, </inglise>
<eesti> Ministrid </eesti>
<inglise> Invite the Committee on Customs Valuation established under the Agreement on Implementation of Article VII of GATT 1994 to take the following decision: </inglise>
<eesti> kutsuvad GATT 1994 VII artikli rakendamise lepingu alusel asutatud tolliv&auml;&auml;rtuse komiteed vastu v&otilde;tma j&auml;rgmist otsust. </eesti>
<inglise> The Committee on Customs Valuation, </inglise>
<eesti> Tolliv&auml;&auml;rtuse komitee, </eesti>
<inglise> Reaffirming that the transaction value is the primary basis of valuation under the Agreement on Implementation of Article VII of GATT 1994 (hereinafter referred to as the "Agreement"); </inglise>
<eesti> kinnitades veel kord, et GATT 1994 VII artikli rakendamise lepingus (edaspidi "leping") on hindamise p&otilde;hialuseks tehinguv&auml;&auml;rtus; </eesti>
<inglise> Recognizing that the customs administration may have to address cases where it has reason to doubt the truth or accuracy of the particulars or of documents produced by traders in support of a declared value; </inglise>
<eesti> t&otilde;dedes, et tollil v&otilde;ib tulla tegemist juhtumitega, mille puhul on p&otilde;hjust kahelda nende &uuml;ksikasjade v&otilde;i dokumentide &otilde;igsuses v&otilde;i t&auml;psuses, mille kaubandusettev&otilde;tjad on esitanud deklareeritud v&auml;&auml;rtuse t&otilde;enduseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Emphasizing that in so doing the customs administration should not prejudice the legitimate commercial interests of traders; </inglise>
<eesti> r&otilde;hutades, et nii toimides ei tohiks toll kahjustada kaubandusettev&otilde;tjate &otilde;igustatud kaubandushuve; </eesti>
<inglise> Taking into account Article 17 of the Agreement, paragraph 6 of Annex III to the Agreement, and the relevant decisions of the Technical Committee on Customs Valuation; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse lepingu artiklit 17, lepingu III lisa punkti 6 ja tolliv&auml;&auml;rtuse m&auml;&auml;ramise tehnilise komitee asjakohaseid otsuseid, </eesti>
<inglise> Decides as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> otsustab j&auml;rgmist: </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> When a declaration has been presented and where the customs administration has reason to doubt the truth or accuracy of the particulars or of documents produced in support of this declaration, the customs administration may ask the importer to provide further explanation, including documents or other evidence, that the declared value represents the total amount actually paid or payable for the imported goods, adjusted in accordance with the provisions of Article 8. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui on esitatud deklaratsioon, mille puhul tollil on p&otilde;hjust kahelda selle deklaratsiooni toetuseks esitatud &uuml;ksikasjade v&otilde;i dokumentide &otilde;igsuses v&otilde;i t&auml;psuses, v&otilde;ib toll n&otilde;uda importijalt lisaselgituste, sealhulgas dokumentide v&otilde;i muu t&otilde;endusmaterjali esitamist selle kohta, et deklareeritud v&auml;&auml;rtus kujutab imporditud kauba eest tegelikult makstud v&otilde;i maksmisele kuuluvat &uuml;ldsummat, mida on korrigeeritud artikli 8 s&auml;tete kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise> If, after receiving further information, or in the absence of a response, the customs administration still has reasonable doubts about the truth or accuracy of the declared value, it may, bearing in mind the provisions of Article 11, be deemed that the customs value of the imported goods cannot be determined under the provisions of Article 1. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui p&auml;rast lisateabe saamist v&otilde;i vastuse puudumisel on tollil ikka veel p&otilde;hjendatud kahtlusi deklareeritud v&auml;&auml;rtuse &otilde;igsuses v&otilde;i t&auml;psuses, v&otilde;ib ta artikli 11 s&auml;tteid silmas pidades j&auml;reldada, et importkauba tolliv&auml;&auml;rtust ei saa artikli 1 s&auml;tete alusel kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata. </eesti>
<inglise> Before taking a final decision, the customs administration shall communicate to the importer, in writing if requested, its grounds for doubting the truth or accuracy of the particulars or documents produced and the importer shall be given a reasonable opportunity to respond. </inglise>
<eesti> Enne l&otilde;pliku otsuse tegemist edastab toll importijale taotluse korral esitatud &uuml;ksikasjade v&otilde;i dokumentide &otilde;igsuses v&otilde;i t&auml;psuses kahtlemise kirjaliku p&otilde;hjenduse ning importijale antakse v&otilde;imalus vastata. </eesti>
<inglise> When a final decision is made, the customs administration shall communicate to the importer in writing its decision and the grounds therefor. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui l&otilde;plik otsus on tehtud, edastab toll importijale kirjalikult oma otsuse ja p&otilde;hjenduse. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> It is entirely appropriate in applying the Agreement for one Member to assist another Member on mutually agreed terms. </inglise>
<eesti> Lepingu kohaldamisel on t&auml;iesti asjakohane, et &uuml;ks liige abistab teist vastastikku kokkulepitud tingimustel. </eesti>
 